  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Access to Modern Energy &#x2013; Lightning for Learning</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Lightning for Learning:Since 2014 UNICEF Sudan has been working on a successful e-learning programme. Children in remote communities, far away from the nearest school, learn basic literacy and numeracy skills through a tablet based game. Children learn in a community center where both lighting and tablets are powered by solar systems.Building on this project, UNICEF Sudan and Practical Action will pilot a more market oriented approach, by distributing 30 solar lights to 10 remote communities (300 in total). The lights can be used by children to study at home or by women to start income generating activities from home. Moreover, the lights provide a phone charger, increasing connectivity within these remote communities.The solar lights are owned by women in the community, who will in turn provide them to households for a set fee, providing a source of income and revolving funds to extend the use of solar systems. Practical Action will train the women in entrepreneurship and basic accounting, while UNICEF will teach youth in maintenance of the solar lights, in doing so creating job opportunities.Through our approach we believe we can build momentum in order to scale up the use of solar energy and other types of modern energy sources beyond Lightning for Learning.</narrative>
  </description>
